# Git Workflow

## Branch Rules

- **NEVER** commit or push directly to `main` or `master`
- **ALWAYS** create a feature branch: `git checkout -b {type}/{description}`
- Branch prefixes: `feature/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, `refactor/`, `test/`, `chore/`, `hotfix/`

## Commit Messages

Format: `{type}: {short description}`

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`

## Security

Never commit: `.env`, API keys, OAuth secrets, database passwords, `users/` directory contents.

## Workflow

```
git checkout main && git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/your-feature
# make changes, test locally
git add -A && git commit -m "feat: description"
git push origin feature/your-feature
# user creates PR and merges
```
